                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "defensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>A torn trio ordinarily has three severed limbs tethered to a central point by near-incorporeal ropes. A limb is essentially cut away from the central point and rendered nonfunctional each time the torn quartet loses 60 Hit Points (so at 120 Hit Points, the torn quartet has two functional limbs, at 60 Hit Points, it has one functional limb). Each functioning limb can @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.Grapple] separate creatures within reach, or multiple functioning limbs can Grapple the same creature; for each additional limb used to Grapple a creature, the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.actionspf2e.Item.Escape] DC increases by 2.</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
